snippet: Demonstrations against rising prices and economic hardship erupted Monday into rioting against the Palestinian Authority, posing a new challenge to the Western-backed government.
abstract: Demonstrations in West Bank against rising prices and economic hardship erupt into rioting against the Palestinian Authority, posing new challenge to the Western-backed government that has worked to promote stability; public anger has mostly been directed at Prime Min Salam Fayyad.
lead_paragraph: Demonstrations against rising prices and economic hardship erupted Monday into rioting against the Palestinian Authority, posing a new challenge to the Western-backed government.

headline.seo: Spreading Palestinian Protests Focus on Leaders
